Description: The rest on the flight into Egypt; the Virgin seated next to a tree in foreground, turned to left and looking at the infant Christ in her arms; St Joseph seated on the ground at far r, asleep; landscape background. Woodcut
Curator's comments: BM also has another impression set in a border with putti climbing vine and playing instruments, see Hollstein 1186 and BM E,8.7.
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / German engravings, etchings and woodcuts c.1400-1700 (9)
Dodgson 1903, 1911 / Catalogue of Early German and Flemish Woodcuts in the BM, 2 vols (II.32.85)
Acquisition notes: The print is laid down and there is no indication of the provenance on the mount.
